By Adedayo Akinwale The All Progressives Congress (APC) has commended President Muhammadu Buhari for practically leading from the front and ensuring that the abducted Kankara schoolboys regained their freedom. The Acting Deputy National Publicity Secretary of the party, Mr. Yekini Nabena, in a statement issued Friday said, while the opposition elements were out to make some political gains, the President was tireless having sleepless nights on the solution to the sad development. He said APC as a party thanked God for wisdom to successfully free the innocent boys from their abductors, saying, “this, indeed has shown the difference. Nabena added: “The All Progressives Congress (APC) is extremely happy at the cheering news that the abducted Kankara students have been released to the Katsina state government. “The party specifically commend President Muhammadu Buhari for practically leading from the front and remained in Kastina until the abducted boys regained their freedom. “We also thank the Kastina state governor and all the security agencies for their proactiveness, unity of purpose and their involvement in the rescue mission.” Nabena noted that APC under the leadership of its Chairman, Caretaker/Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee, Governor Mai Mala Buni, urged all the security agencies to continue to live up to the expectations and restore public confidence in their ability to secure the lives and property of Nigerians. He called on Nigerians to continue to cooperate and provide relevant information for the security agencies to work on. Nabena said there was need to have confidence in this administration being competently led by PresidentBuhari.